.TH man 1 "19 Dec 2014" "@AAX_UTILS_MAJOR_VERSION@.@AAX_UTILS_MINOR_VERSION@.@AAX_UTILS_MICRO_VERSION@" "aaxplay man page"
.SH NAME
aaxplay \- Plays audio from a file or from an audio input device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aaxplay
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Plays audio from a file or from an audio input device.
Optionally writes the audio to an output file.
.TP
\fB\-i\f, \fB\-\-input \fRFILE\fR
playback audio from a file
.TP
\fB\-i\f, \fB\-\-capture \fRDEVICE\fR
capture from an audio device
.TP
\fB\-d\f, \fB\-\-device \fRDEVICE\fR
playback device (optional)
.TP
\fB\-o\f, \fB\-\-output \fRFILE\fR
also write the audio to a file (optional)
.TP
\fB\-b\f, \fB\-\-batch
process as fast as possible (file out only)
.TP
\fB\-v,\f \fB\-\-verbose
show extra playback information
.TP
\fB\-h\f, \fB\-\-help
print this message and exit
.PP
Audio will always be sent to the (default) audio device,
writing to an output file is fully optional.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Erik Hofman (info@adalin.com)
.SH SEE ALSO
